# Security Standards

## Authentication

- Stateless only: `SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS`
- Current: API key via `X-API-Key` header (placeholder — JWT planned)
- All `/api/v1/chat/**` requires authenticated principal
- Actuator: only `health` and `info` are public

## Prompt Firewall

- Every user prompt passes through `PromptFirewall.validate()` before LLM call
- New threat patterns → add to `PromptFirewall.BLOCKED_PATTERNS`
- Reject with `PromptFirewallException`, never silently strip content

## Headers (enforced in SecurityConfig)

- Content-Security-Policy: `default-src 'self'`
- X-Frame-Options: DENY
- HSTS with includeSubDomains
- Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

## Secrets & Data

- No hardcoded secrets — use `${ENV_VAR:default}` in `application.yml`
- `messages.content` is a future encryption target — do not log it
- Error responses: no stack traces, no internal messages (`server.error.*` is locked down)

## Adding Auth Features

- Work in `auth/` package only
- Update `SecurityConfig` filter chain
- Do not weaken existing endpoint protection to add new features
